<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 29 日星期一 13:20:13 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Scientist Warns of Looming 'Existential Threat' as Hyper-Intelligent AI 'Could Decide to Take Over']]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110772797" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106372/86/1063728691_0:0:1920:1280_1440x900_80_0_1_519688962cc01c226032990d683920ba.jpg?source-sid=cc_0" data-photoview-image-id="1063728690" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/scientist-warns-of-looming-existential-threat-as-hyper-intelligent-ai-could-decide-to-take-over-1110772797.html?share-img=1063728690"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright"><a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> //</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">人工智能</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="cc_0" alt="Artificial Intelligence - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="人工智能" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106372/86/1063728691_0:100:1920:1180_1920x0_80_0_0_8b7701668f9ca61ab6b2c81fdeeff215.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106372/86/1063728691_0:100:1920:1180_640x0_80_0_0_51c43b130326a3e662011985463ab11a.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106372/86/1063728691_0:100:1920:1180_1280x0_80_0_0_b63fb707b44b2a56aff172a469ccc326.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/106372/86/1063728691_0:100:1920:1180_1920x0_80_0_0_8b7701668f9ca61ab6b2c81fdeeff215.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> / / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">斯韦特兰娜·埃基缅科</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_svetlana_ekimenko/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:s.ekimenko@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">Geoffrey Hinton 是一位英裔加拿大计算机科学家，他在人工神经网络领域的努力为他赢得了“人工智能教父”的绰号，他最近加入了全世界的声音合唱，警告说如果人工智能变得比人类更聪明，它可能会造成灾难性的后果。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230508/ai-could-pose-more-urgent-threat-than-climate-change-pioneer-says-1110205651.html#:~:text=AI%20Could%20Pose%20%27More%20Urgent%27%20Threat%20Than%20Climate%20Change%2C%20Pioneer%20Says" target="_blank">AI 先驱 Geoffrey Hinton</a>越来越对人工智能 (AI) 工具变得“多么智能”感到“不安”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “这些东西可能变得比我们更聪明，并可能决定接管，我们现在需要担心我们如何防止这种情况发生，”这位因其研究获得了计算机科学和计算机机械领域最负盛名的奖项的人，告诉美国广播节目的主持人。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110772797" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/scientist-warns-of-looming-existential-threat-as-hyper-intelligent-ai-could-decide-to-take-over-1110772797.html?share-block=1110772799" data-title="&amp;quot;These things could get more intelligent than us and could decide to take over, and we need to worry now about how we prevent that happening,&amp;quot; the man, who has received the most prestigious award in computer science and computing machinery for his research, told the hosts of a US radio show."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位现居加拿大多伦多的学者在其 50 年的职业生涯中致力于开发尖端人工智能。最近，这位 75 岁的老人在谷歌工作，但在 5 月初离开了其母公司 Alphabet。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我离开是为了谈论人工智能的危险，而不考虑这对谷歌的影响，”他在<a href="https://twitter.com/geoffreyhinton/status/1652993570721210372" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">推特上写道</a>。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110772797" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/scientist-warns-of-looming-existential-threat-as-hyper-intelligent-ai-could-decide-to-take-over-1110772797.html?share-block=1110773000" data-title="“I left so that I could talk about the dangers of AI without considering how this impacts Google,” he had tweeted."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">从那以后，他一直在对他帮助开发的技术的“危险”提出警告。在新的采访中，Hinton 回忆起在谷歌测试聊天机器人时——PaLM 模型——<strong>它似乎能理解他讲的一个笑话</strong>。 PaLM（Pathways Language Model）是谷歌人工智能开发的一种大型语言模型，自发布更新的下一代模型 PaLM 2 以来，这家科技巨头拥有“改进的多语言、推理和编码能力”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在这种互动过程中，这位科学家突然意识到，人工智能可能“<em>超越</em>”人类的时代并不遥远。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “很长一段时间以来，我一直认为我们距离那个目标还有 30 到 50 年的时间。所以我认为这与拥有比人类更高的一般智力的事物相去甚远。现在，我认为我们可能更接近了，也许只是五年后，”欣顿说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110772797" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/scientist-warns-of-looming-existential-threat-as-hyper-intelligent-ai-could-decide-to-take-over-1110772797.html?share-block=1110772805" data-title="&quot;I thought for a long time that we were, like, 30 to 50 years away from that. So I call that far away from something that's got greater general intelligence than a person. Now, I think we may be much closer, maybe only five years away from that,&quot; Hinton said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h2"><h2 class="article__h2"> “生存威胁”</h2></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">参考<a href="https://www.foxnews.com/category/tech/artificial-intelligence" target="_blank">OpenAI 的 ChatGPT 等聊天机器人</a>，Hinton 强调说，AI 经过训练可以理解或学习人类可以处理的任何智力任务。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “<em>我并不是说它有知觉</em>，”他谈到人工智能时说，但补充道，“<em>我也不是说它没有知觉。</em> ”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他驳斥了反对者关于人工智能危险的色彩和呼声被夸大的说法，他补充说这不是科幻小说中的问题，而是一个“<em>可能很快就会到来的严重问题，政客们需要考虑什么现在就去做。”</em> </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “他们当然可以思考，他们当然可以理解事物。而且，有些人的意思是，‘它有主观经验吗？’我认为，如果我们引入主观体验的问题，它只会掩盖整个问题，你会卷入各种关于人们是什么样子的半宗教事物。所以，让我们避免这种情况，”该男子继续说道。 ，在“谷歌十年的贡献”中，他被誉为“在人工智能领域取得了基础性突破”。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110772797" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/scientist-warns-of-looming-existential-threat-as-hyper-intelligent-ai-could-decide-to-take-over-1110772797.html?share-block=1110773001" data-title="&amp;quot;They can certainly think and they can certainly understand things. And, some people by sentient mean, ‘Does it have subjective experience?’ I think if we bring in the issue of subjective experience, it just clouds the whole issue and you get involved in all sorts of things that are sort of semi-religious about what people are like. So, let&amp;#x27;s avoid that,&amp;quot; continued the man, who has been hailed as making &amp;quot;foundational breakthroughs in AI” amid “decade of contributions at Google.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Hinton 发出警告之际，越来越多的技术领导者对<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230514/stakes-couldnt-be-higher-unbridled-super-intelligent-ai-could-wipe-out-humanity-1110344362.html#:~:text=%27Stakes%20Couldn%E2%80%99t%20Be%20Higher%27%3A%20Unbridled%20Super%2DIntelligent%20AI%20Could%20%27Wipe%20Out%27%20Humanity" target="_blank">超智能人工智能的潜在危险</a>敲响了警钟。特斯拉首席执行官埃隆马斯克、人工智能先驱约书亚亨吉奥和斯图尔特罗素以及其他数千人在 4 月份签署了一封信，呼吁暂停六个月开发更强大的人工智能系统。然而，Hinton 并不是这封信的签署人，因为他认为在当前竞争激烈的 AI 世界中暂停是不现实的。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我只想对存在的威胁发出警报，”这位计算机科学家总结道。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110772797" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/scientist-warns-of-looming-existential-threat-as-hyper-intelligent-ai-could-decide-to-take-over-1110772797.html?share-block=1110773300" data-title="&quot;All I want to do is just sound the alarm about the existential threat,&quot; the computer scientist concluded."></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 29 May 2023 12:58:27 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/scientist-warns-of-looming-existential-threat-as-hyper-intelligent-ai-could-decide-to-take-over-1110772797.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/scientist-warns-of-looming-existential-threat-as-hyper-intelligent-ai-could-decide-to-take-over-1110772797.html<category>超越政治</category><category>人工智能 (AI)</category><category>罗伯特·欣顿</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>谷歌</category><category>开放人工智能</category><category>埃隆·马斯克</category><category>神经网络</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[OSCE Observers Believe Turkish Voters Had Opportunity to Choose Between Real Alternatives]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110774402" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1c/1110647958_0:0:3089:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_b8faef0330cef3cb6f99b890d6bae4e6.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110647940" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/osce-observers-believe-turkish-voters-had-opportunity-to-choose-between-real-alternatives-1110774402.html?share-img=1110647940"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Pavel Bednyakov</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">现任土耳其总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安的支持者在安卡拉的一次集会上。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Supporters of incumbent Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan at a rally in Ankara. - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="现任土耳其总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安的支持者在安卡拉的一次集会上。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1c/1110647958_0:156:3089:1894_1920x0_80_0_0_22b3f5ef394d887863bbfac968300acd.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1c/1110647958_0:156:3089:1894_640x0_80_0_0_18b5dc64b0f69a6c154cb9abd44ccbbb.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1c/1110647958_0:156:3089:1894_1280x0_80_0_0_f5ce4dbecc0aed6aec6614c58ba4c321.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/1c/1110647958_0:156:3089:1894_1920x0_80_0_0_22b3f5ef394d887863bbfac968300acd.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / 帕维尔贝德尼亚科夫</div>/ </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：欧洲安全与合作组织（欧安组织）周一表示，欧洲安全与合作组织（欧安组织）的观察员认为，土耳其的总统选举让公民可以在真正的选择之间做出选择。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “Turkiye 的第二轮总统选举进行得很好，让选民有机会在真正的政治选择之间做出选择，但其特点是在竞选期间越来越多的煽动性和歧视性语言。媒体偏见和对言论自由的持续限制造成了不公平的竞争国际观察员在今天的一份声明中说，并助长了现任者的不正当优势，”欧安组织的声明说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">土耳其最高选举委员会周日表示，现任总统雷杰普·塔伊普· <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230528/erdogan-clinches-victory-in-turkiyes-presidential-runoff-1110751521.html" target="_blank">埃尔多安以52.14%的选票赢得第二轮</a>总统选举。最终结果最早将于 6 月 1 日公布。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 29 May 2023 12:58:24 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/osce-observers-believe-turkish-voters-had-opportunity-to-choose-between-real-alternatives-1110774402.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/osce-observers-believe-turkish-voters-had-opportunity-to-choose-between-real-alternatives-1110774402.html<category>世界</category><category>雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安</category><category>欧安组织</category><category>欧洲安全与合作组织</category><category>突厥耶</category><category>2023 年土耳其总统选举</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Trade in National Currencies to Have 'Healing Effect' on Global Economy – Lavrov]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110773930" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/02/0f/1107460512_0:0:3128:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_74db30c0e8649bb895de8eae22554083.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1107460494" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/trade-in-national-currencies-to-have-healing-effect-on-global-economy--lavrov-1110773930.html?share-img=1107460494"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 俄罗斯外交部新闻处</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">俄罗斯外交部长谢尔盖拉夫罗夫，2023 年 2 月 10 日</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov, February 10, 2023 - Sputnik International, 1920, 29.05.2023" title="俄罗斯外交部长谢尔盖拉夫罗夫，2023 年 2 月 10 日" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/02/0f/1107460512_0:0:3128:1761_1920x0_80_0_0_f1d2255ff4b87d1e85102f1ee8fdda86.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/02/0f/1107460512_0:0:3128:1761_640x0_80_0_0_bf7f1585a5d4efcf352b963bf1b92aa9.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/02/0f/1107460512_0:0:3128:1761_1280x0_80_0_0_43f1852575f36dafa904440155c5423a.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/02/0f/1107460512_0:0:3128:1761_1920x0_80_0_0_f1d2255ff4b87d1e85102f1ee8fdda86.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 俄罗斯外交部新闻处</div>/ </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据内罗毕（人造卫星）网报道：俄罗斯外交部长谢尔盖·拉夫罗夫周一表示，国家间向以本国货币进行交易的过渡将对全球经济和国际贸易产生“治愈作用”。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">拉夫罗夫在访问肯尼亚期间对记者说：“这是一个客观的过程，它将获得动力，我们相信它将对世界经济、国际贸易以及经济和投资关系产生治愈作用。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位部长还指出，俄罗斯和肯尼亚之间的结算仍然以美元结算，因为双边贸易额还没有那么大，目前还不到 4 亿美元，并补充说各国将来肯定会转向本国货币。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “这不仅适用于非洲，也适用于拉丁美洲和我们在亚洲的合作伙伴，包括伊朗、印度和中国。我们已经在积极转向以本国货币结算。美元的份额 [在俄罗斯的贸易中]正在逐渐下降，”他说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110773930" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/trade-in-national-currencies-to-have-healing-effect-on-global-economy--lavrov-1110773930.html?share-block=1110773933" data-title="&quot;This applies not only to Africa, but also to Latin America and our partners in Asia, with Iran, with India, and with China. We are already actively shifting to settlements in national currencies. The share of the dollar [in Russia’s trade] is gradually declining,&quot; he said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">当天早些时候， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230529/lavrov-arrives-in-nairobi-to-discuss-kenya-ties-with-nations-president--fm-1110766713.html" target="_blank">拉夫罗夫</a>抵达肯尼亚首都内罗毕进行工作访问。俄罗斯外长上一次访问肯尼亚是在2010年，拉夫罗夫此次访问是他在过去12个月内第四次访问非洲。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 29 May 2023 12:46:34 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/trade-in-national-currencies-to-have-healing-effect-on-global-economy--lavrov-1110773930.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230529/trade-in-national-currencies-to-have-healing-effect-on-global-economy--lavrov-1110773930.html<category>经济</category><category>肯尼亚</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>谢尔盖·拉夫罗夫</category><category>本国货币</category></item></channel></rss>